1. React state
-----------------
   -  State generally refers to data or properties that need to be tracking in an application.
   -  The React useState Hook allows us to track state in a function component.


useState()
----------- 

    Syntax :
    -------
        const [currentState, setterState] = useState(initalValue);

            - currentState   =  Storage container  
            - setterState   =  Modifier method.

        useState accepts an initial state and returns two values:

           


     Example:
     -------
        function FC() { 
            const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

            return <div>
                <h1> Your count is  {count} </h1>
            </div>


        }

Note :-
--------


        -  State is focued on anything update current item only 
        -  If you trying to update any array or object that time facing this problem

        Solution : - When you have try to update object or state first you need to copy existing state after you can modify
        Current state.


      
Example
--------

         function FC() { 
            const [fruits, setFruits] = useState(['apple','orange','stabery']);

            const addFruit = () => {
                setFruits([...fruits,'pineapple'])
            }

            return <div>
                <h1> Your fruits is  {fruits} </h1>
                <button onClick = {addFruit}> Add Fruit </button>
            </div>


        }




